		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>We derive a second-order ordinary differential equation (ODE), which is the limit of Nesterov&apos;s accelerated gradient method. This ODE exhibits approximate equivalence to Nesterov&apos;s scheme and thus can serve as a tool for analysis. We show that the continuous time ODE allows for a better understanding of Nesterov&apos;s scheme. As a byproduct, we obtain a family of schemes with similar convergence rates. The ODE interpretation also suggests restarting Nesterov&apos;s scheme leading to an algorithm, which can be rigorously proven to converge at a linear rate whenever the objective is strongly convex.</p>
			</abstract>
